    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "24. Then David came to Mahanaim—in the high eastern country of Gilead, the seat of Ish-bosheth's government.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Absalom passed over Jordan—It is not said how long an interval elapsed, but there must have been sufficient time to make the intended levy throughout the kingdom.",
        "children": []
      }
